<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="48f3198c-b28b-5cfb-8bec-b3f25bfa6691" activityNameId="707467f5-e8ac-470d-b4db-08ed770f70d4" parentActivityId="32f35cde-d320-564f-af18-d19912cae890" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">flux production, for wave soldering</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From reception of raw materials at the factory gate.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with 1 kg of flux for wave soldering. This dataset includes only the raw materials (i.e. the main inputs) of an example of a wave solder flux. No information about mixing processes, waste and emissions produced are included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of a wave solder flux. In the through-hole mounting technology, cleaning with a special flux is done after placement of the components, before the actual soldering process takes place. In soldering of metals, flux serves a threefold purpose: it removes oxidation from the surfaces to be soldered, it seals out air thus preventing further oxidation, and by facilitating amalgamation, improves wetting characteristics of the liquid solder. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This dataset is based on a flux that is currently used in the wave solder process of the electronics industry. It contains only information about the ingredients, based on information in a Material Safety Data Sheet of a producer of wave solder fluxes (Indium Coorperation, 2004). Electricity consumption for mixing is approximated based on data from a large chemical plant (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Hischier R., Classen M., Lehmann M. and Scharnhorst W. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Electric and Electronic Equipment: Production, Use and Disposal. ecoinvent report No. 18. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Indium Corporation (2004) Indium High Grade Wave Solder Flux #1085 - Material Data Safety Sheet. The Indium Corporation of America, Utica (NY, USA)</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="49e37174-49ec-45f8-bcbf-3220772406a2">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2029:Manufacture of other chemical products n.e.c.</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The inventory is modelled for the world. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Mixture used as wave solder flux in the electronics industry.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2005-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time of publications. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
